
Frame469 Component - Readme

This component was created to display a contact or "Happy to Help" section referencing an example design with phone, fax, email, and address details, plus a CTA button. The data is stored in Sanity as "frame469" type with fields for heading, description, contact info, and an optional map.

Key Points:
- The "default" variant displays the info in two columns
- The "xDemo" variant showcases mock data for demonstration
- The data fields allow editors to change phone, fax, email, address lines, and CTA label/link
- The upsertDemoData script can create a sample page titled "frame469" to quickly test in Sanity

Usage:
1. Add "frame469" to a page in the Sanity Studio
2. Provide the heading, description, cta fields, phone/fax/email, address lines as needed
3. Optionally toggle showMap if you want to display a map (dummy placeholder in code)
4. The "demoVariant" uses static data for demonstration
5. The "frame469DefaultVariant" uses real data from the CMS
